<br>
My personal take on rampage is that it takes the top 3-4 people on the hate list that happen to be in within a certain range.<br>
<br>
I am a bard and i can basicly walk in and out of rampage range during a fight. If i move in close to melee, i get rampaged if i move out, i don't. (I just need to make sure i don't get rampaged down to below 2 bubbles of health)<br>
<br>
One thing i don't know is if me being out of range means someone else gets rampaged, or if by being out of range, noone else gets rampaged.<br>
<br>
Alot of misconceptions is that its really not due to hate which it is in my opinion. People who are ressed in may not be on the hate list but what people forget is that they are ressed in under 2  bubbles of health which is frenzy level. Monsters will automaticly target players who are low health.<br>
<br>
At one time when rampage was first introduced, there didn't seem to be any range on it, people would be rampaged halfwy across the zone, but lately this doesn't seem to be the case at all.<br>
<br>
I can't give difinitive answers but i can suggest this:<br>
<br>
People who don't want to be rampaged, stay as far away from the actual fight as you can. Clerics heal from max range.<br>
Nukers nuke from max range. Bards need to be careful as aoe songs can easily put you on the rampage list, and pretty much anyone without a cleric tasked to them, one or two rampages puts them at frenzy health (under 2 bubbles) which will make the monster turn on them with their regular melee attacks.<br>
